.nh
.TH "LZR" "1" "Jan 2026" "lazyray" "lazyray Manual"

.SH NAME
lzr-tunnel-trust - Pin or re-pin a profile's SSH host key


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBlzr tunnel trust  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Capture the SSH host key of a profile's server, show its SHA256 fingerprint, and pin it into the profile after explicit confirmation.

.PP
Verify the fingerprint out-of-band before confirming (on the server: ssh-keygen -lf /etc/ssh/ssh\fIhost\fP*.pub). With --fingerprint the command is non-interactive: only captured keys whose fingerprints match the provided values are pinned, and a value that matches nothing is an error. Re-running the command replaces a previous pin (shown as "old") after the same confirmation. Pinning via a dedicated known_hosts disables OpenSSH's automatic host-key rotation, so re-run this command when the server legitimately rotates its keys.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--fingerprint\fP=[]
	pin only captured keys matching this SHA256 fingerprint (repeatable; enables non-interactive pinning)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for trust


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  lzr tunnel trust ru
  lzr tunnel trust ru --fingerprint SHA256:mVN1EX9nGiimZzXFqXTZHrpx5RCasCMEEyBGavrfBFo
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBlzr-tunnel(1)\fP
